= 64th Mathematik-Olympiade Round 3 Question 4 - 9-10th Class

Find all solutions $(x, y)$ of the system of equations

$
	x^3 + x^2 y &= 9(x + y) \
	y^3 - x y^2 &= 4(y - x)
$

== Solution

Factorising $x^2$ in the first equation and $y^2$ in the second gives the following:

$
	&(1): &x^2(x + y) &= 9(x + y) \
	&(2): &y^2(y - x) &= 4(y - x) \
	\
	\
	(1) &<==> &x^2(x + y) - 9(x + y) &= 0 \
	&<==> &(x^2 - 9)(x + y) &= 0 \
	&<==> &(x - 3)(x + 3)(x + y) &= 0 \
	&<==> &x - 3 = 0 "or" x + 3 &= 0 "or" x + y = 0 \
	&<==> &x = 3 "or" x &= -3 "or" x = -y \
	\
	\
	(2) &<==> &y^2(y - x) - 4(y - x) &= 0 \
	&<==> &(y^2 - 4)(y - x) &= 0 \
	&<==> &(y - 2)(y + 2)(y - x) &= 0 \
	&<==> &y - 2 = 0 "or" y + 2 &= 0 "or" y - x = 0 \
	&<==> &y = 2 "or" y &= -2 "or" y = x \
$

\

$
	==> (x, y) in {(3, 2), (3, -2), (-3, 2), (-3, -2), (3, 3), (-3, -3), (2, -2), (-2, 2), (0, 0)}
$
